('Pierre. L.', 'Pierre.', 'L.', 'General Manager at Chatrium Grand Bangkok', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/pierre-l-96384552', 'pierre-l-96384552', $${"about": "Pierre is the General Manager of Chatrium Grand Bangkok, a distinguished 562-room luxury hotel situated in Bangkok’s vibrant Siam district, with direct access to Siam Paragon, one of Asia’s most iconic lifestyle destinations.\n\nDesigned for those seeking freedom and serenity in the heart of the city, Chatrium Grand Bangkok offers the perfect setting for every type of stay from business travel and family getaways to romantic escapes. \n\nChatrium Grand Bangkok’s Awards \n\nLuxury Hotel Awards: 2024\n- Luxury Business Hotel – Country Winner\n- Luxury City Hotel – Regional Winner\n\nMichelin Star Awards: 2025\n- 1 Star - Etcha\n\nGM Awards: 2025 \n- The Most Influential General Managers, Thailand by CMO Asia Awards \n\nAs General Manager, Pierre oversees the hotel’s daily operations, strategic development, commercial performance, and the continued elevation of guest experiences. \n\nWith 18 years of international experience in luxury tourism and hospitality, Pierre has held key roles across renowned properties worldwide. His expertise spans pre-openings, rebranding's, refurbishments, and the successful navigation of complex operational landscapes.\n\nPrior to joining Chatrium Grand Bangkok, Pierre was Resort Manager at One&Only Reethi Rah in the Maldives, one of the world’s most iconic ultra-luxury resorts.\n\nPierre’s academic background includes  degrees in social sciences and certifications in hospitality management. His academic thesis focused on cultural geography, with a particular emphasis on pre-openings, franchise dynamics, and cross-cultural leadership within the hospitality sector.\n\nDriven by a strong belief that “hospitality is a mission of creating memorable experiences,” Pierre’s goal is to build an environment where both guests and colleagues feel recognized, valued, and genuinely welcomed, eve